    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - DISASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (1X707 MODELS)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY (1X707 MODELS)</title>
        <para>When removing limit washers, spacers and gears, note their location. Keep internal- splined washers and
            external-splined spacers with the gear from which they were removed. There is only one limit washer and one
            spacer belonging to each gear.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed sliding clutch from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302083">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302083" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302083" filename="../figg13/g1302083.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. 2nd - 3rd Speed Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the key from the mainshaft keyway (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302084">Figure 84</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302084" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302084" filename="../figg13/g1302084.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 84. Mainshaft Keyway</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd speed gear, washer and limit washer. Remove 2nd speed gear and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302085">Figure 85</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302085" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302085" filename="../figg13/g1302085.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 85. 3rd &#38; 2nd Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear spacer from the mainshaft rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302085">Figure 85</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft in a vertical position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302086">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302086" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302086" filename="../figg13/g1302086.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 86. Mainshaft In Vertical Position</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the mainshaft rear, pull the mainshaft key from the mainshaft keyway (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302086">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the reverse gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove (Figure (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302087">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302087">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302087" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302087" filename="../figg13/g1302087.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 87. Mainshaft Splines</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the LO-reverse speed clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302088">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302088" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302088" filename="../figg13/g1302088.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 88. LO- Reverse Speed Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a small screwdriver to turn the LO gear limit washer to align its splines with the
                mainshaft. Remove LO gear, limit washer and spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302089">Figure 89</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302089" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302089" filename="../figg13/g1302089.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. LO Gear Limit Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove each remaining gear, limit washer and spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302089">Figure 89</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each gear I.D. snap ring; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the roll pin; replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302090">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302090" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302090" filename="../figg13/g1302090.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Inspect Roll Pin</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
